SUMMARY:Deadline: Stimuleringsfonds: Activity Programme Grant 2027-2028
DESCRIPTION:Two-year activity-programme funding from the Creative Industrie
 s Fund NL for organisations active in design\, digital culture or architec
 ture. Supports a coherent multi-year programme of activities running acros
 s 2027 and 2028 (rather than single projects). The funding underwrites a p
 ortion of the organisation's annual programme budget\, giving recipients p
 lanning stability over the two-year period. Application window 13 May - 15
  June 2026. EUR 50\,000 to EUR 125\,000 per year per organisation\, depend
 ing on the scale and ambition of the proposed programme. ELIGIBILITY: cult
 ural and creative-industries organisations established in the Netherlands 
 working in design\, digital culture or architecture\; a distinct scheme fr
 om the Fund's annual project grants\, festival rounds and voucher schemes.
 \n\nOrganisation: Stimuleringsfonds Creatieve Industrie (Creative Industri
 es Fund NL)\nLocation: Netherlands\nAward: EUR 50\,000 to EUR 125\,000 per
  year for the 2027 and 2028 calendar years\nDuration: Two years\, 2027 and
  2028\n\nMore: https://www.stimuleringsfonds.nl/en/news/opening-and-closin
 g-dates-2026
URL:https://www.stimuleringsfonds.nl/en/news/opening-and-closing-dates-2026
LOCATION:Netherlands
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:stroom-den-haag-pro-grants-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260529T085824Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260531
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260601
SUMMARY:Deadline: Stroom Den Haag: PRO Grants 2026 (Research / Projects / P
 rogrammes / Investment)
DESCRIPTION:Stroom Den Haag's PRO grants support professional visual artist
 s registered with Stroom in The Hague through four schemes: PRO Research (
 research and development for new work)\, PRO Projects (project realisation
 )\, PRO Programmes (multi-stage artistic programmes spanning research\, pr
 oduction and presentation)\, and PRO Investment (investment in artistic pr
 actice\, e.g. equipment\, studio\, professional development). Three remain
 ing 2026 application rounds: 31 May\, 6 September and 25 October 2026. ELI
 GIBILITY: professional visual artists registered with Stroom in the munici
 pality of The Hague (tightly geographic). Amounts vary by scheme and propo
 sal\, typically EUR 2\,500 to EUR 20\,000+.\n\nOrganisation: Stroom Den Ha
 ag\nLocation: The Hague\, Netherlands (eligibility restricted to professio
 nal visual artists registered with Stroom in the municipality of The Hague
 )\nAward: Four schemes - PRO Research\, PRO Projects\, PRO Programmes\, an
 d PRO Investment - with amounts typically EUR 2\,500 to EUR 20\,000+ depen
 ding on scheme and proposal.\nDuration: Project-based\n\nMore: https://www
 .stroom.nl/en/stroom-for-artists/financial-support/pro-research
URL:https://www.stroom.nl/en/stroom-for-artists/financial-support/pro-resea
 rch
LOCATION:The Hague\, Netherlands (eligibility restricted to professional vi
 sual artists registered with Stroom in the municipality of The Hague)
