SUMMARY:Deadline: IMMA Dwell Here Residency 2027 (One-Year and One-Month)
DESCRIPTION:IMMA's Dwell Here residency programme offers research-led resid
 encies in Dublin across the visual arts\, design\, architecture\, curation
  and related humanities fields\, open to artists and practitioners based i
 n Ireland or internationally. One application covers two formats: a One-Ye
 ar residency (monthly EUR 1\,000 bursary\, free studio and accommodation\,
  travel for non-Ireland residents) and a One-Month residency (EUR 250/week
  stipend\, free room and shared studio\, travel for international particip
 ants). Suited to research\, critical-writing and cross-disciplinary practi
 ce including new-media work. ELIGIBILITY: open internationally\; framed ar
 ound research excellence rather than career stage. Deadline Monday 22 June
  2026\, 14:00 GMT\; a EUR 10 application fee applies via Submittable. See 
 the IMMA open-calls page for the separate one-year and one-month applicati
 on links.\n\nOrganisation: Irish Museum of Modern Art (IMMA)\nLocation: Du
 blin\, Ireland\nAward: Funded. One-Year residency: EUR 1\,000/month bursar
 y for contracted months\, free studio and accommodation\, plus one return 
 journey for residents from outside Ireland. One-Month residency: EUR 250/w
 eek stipend\, free private bedroom and shared studio\, plus a return journ
 ey for international participants. NOTE: EUR 10 application fee (Submittab
 le).\nDuration: One-year or one-month residency during 2027\n\nMore: https
 ://imma.ie/residency-programme/open-calls/
URL:https://imma.ie/residency-programme/open-calls/
LOCATION:Dublin\, Ireland
END:VEVENT
