UID:fpp-residency-exhibition-konstkollektivet-2026@artificialnouveau.github
 .io
DTSTAMP:20260529T085824Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260614
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260615
SUMMARY:Deadline: FPP Residency & Exhibition 2026 (Konstkollektivet / Flowe
 r Power Photography)
DESCRIPTION:Residency and exhibition for visual artists whose practice enga
 ges with experimental\, alternative and/or critical image-making (analogue
  processes\, archives or hybrid approaches)\, with a particular interest i
 n image-making as a way of living and thinking alongside the planet and ot
 her beings\, embracing slowness\, collaboration and more-than-human care. 
 Organised by Konstkollektivet with Flower Power Photography (an artistic r
 esearch project by Sam McCarthy and Lasse Lindqvist on non-violence\, ecol
 ogy and more-than-human ethics)\, Centrum for fotografi\, and Artist in Co
 existence (AiC). Includes a 14-day residency on the island of Orust (3-15 
 August)\, a process presentation\, a workshop contribution at Konstkollekt
 ivet (15-16 August)\, and participation in a group exhibition at Konstpark
 en opening 1 September\, plus accommodation\, an artist fee (7\,000 SEK)\,
  exhibition fee (3\,400 SEK)\, and travel support up to 4\,000 SEK. ELIGIB
 ILITY: European-based visual artists of all ages and nationalities. APPLIC
 ATION: one PDF (max 10MB) with a project proposal/motivation (max 1 page)\
 , artist statement (max 150 words)\, CV (1 page) and portfolio (max 5 page
 s) to residens@konstkollektivet.se\, subject line 'Name_LastName_FPP_Resid
 ency'\, by 14 June 2026.\n\nOrganisation: Konstkollektivet\, with Flower P
 ower Photography\, Centrum for fotografi and Artist in Coexistence (AiC)\n
 Location: Orust and Molndal\, Sweden\nAward: Artist fee 7\,000 SEK plus ex
 hibition fee 3\,400 SEK\, travel support up to 4\,000 SEK (slow travel by 
 train/bus encouraged)\, and accommodation for the whole period. Plus facil
 itation\, mentorship and research support. No application fee. (Amounts in
  SEK\, incl. VAT where applicable.)\nDuration: 14-day residency 3-17 Augus
 t 2026\; group exhibition opens 1 September 2026\n\nMore: https://www.kons
 tkollektivet.se/open-call-fpp-residency-exhibition/
URL:https://www.konstkollektivet.se/open-call-fpp-residency-exhibition/
LOCATION:Orust and Molndal\, Sweden
END:VEVENT
