UID:a4-residency-chengdu-2027-2028@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260529T085824Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260630
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260701
SUMMARY:Deadline: A4 Residency: 2027-2028 International Residency Program (
 Chengdu)
DESCRIPTION:Multidisciplinary international residency at the A4 Residency A
 rt Center in Chengdu\, China\, a global exchange platform integrating crea
 tion\, networking and resources\, which has hosted 335 creators from 44+ c
 ountries since 2011. Residents engage with the art center\, community and 
 city through interdisciplinary\, locally-engaged practice\, supported by A
 4's resource library\, a 'Super Agent' system pairing artists with local r
 esidents\, and a documentation/research programme. Two participation track
 s: a Fully Funded Fellowship (studio\, accommodation\, travel within budge
 t\, RMB 10\,000 production grant\, networking\, media and presentation sup
 port) and a self-funded 'Light Version' (studio and accommodation provided
 \; travel and production self-covered). Residents initiate 1-2 participato
 ry local events and take part in open studios\, field trips and sharing ev
 ents\, with outcomes shown via exhibitions\, performances\, publications o
 r public art. WHO CAN APPLY: multidisciplinary artists (visual\, performin
 g\, music\, film\, sound\, architecture)\, curators\, designers (product\,
  fashion\, spatial\, interactive)\, and interdisciplinary creatives integr
 ating art\, business and culture\; international\, no nationality restrict
 ion. DEADLINES: 2027 recruitment by 30 June 2026\; 2028 year-round recruit
 ment by 31 December 2026. APPLICATION: submit a personal photo\, portfolio
 \, CV and project proposal in both English and Chinese by email (a4residen
 cy@a4am.cn for the funded fellowship\; qiaojiayi@a4residency.com.cn for th
 e Light Version).\n\nOrganisation: A4 Residency Art Center (A4 Art Museum)
 \nLocation: Chengdu\, China\nAward: Two tracks. Fully Funded Fellowship: p
 rivate studio and accommodation\, round-trip economy airfare or 2nd-class 
 train (within a set budget)\, and an RMB 10\,000 production grant\, plus r
 esource networking\, media exposure and presentation opportunities. Light 
 Version: self-funded (studio and accommodation provided\, but the artist c
 overs travel and production costs). No application fee.\nDuration: Approx.
  8 weeks per cycle (Autumn 2027: Jul-Oct\; Spring 2028: Apr-Jun\; Autumn 2
 028: Jul-Oct)\n\nMore: https://www.a4artmuseum.com/en/a4-residencyartcente
 r/residing/latest-recruitment/
URL:https://www.a4artmuseum.com/en/a4-residencyartcenter/residing/latest-re
 cruitment/
LOCATION:Chengdu\, China
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:photovogue-brave-new-visions-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260529T085824Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260911
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260912
SUMMARY:Deadline: PhotoVogue Global Open Call 2026: Brave New Visions - Cre
 ativity as Rebellion
DESCRIPTION:PhotoVogue's global open call invites photographers and video m
 akers to use image-making as a form of rebellion - to challenge indifferen
 ce\, disrupt conventions and expand visual storytelling. It asks not for a
  theme but for a position in relation to the world. Open to photography\, 
 video and multimedia projects across all genres (fashion\, documentary\, p
 ortraiture\, fine art\, experimental). Three artists share $12\,000 in gra
 nts ($6\,000 Outstanding Vision\, $4\,000 Vision\, $2\,000 Rising Voice fo
 r an emerging artist)\, with festival presentation\, potential Vogue publi
 cation and portfolio reviews. ELIGIBILITY: open to all artists worldwide a
 ged 18+\; submissions are free\; previous PhotoVogue applicants may submit
  a new project. SUBMIT: a series of up to 15 images\, or images plus video
  for multimedia\, and/or a 60-second trailer\, via Picter. IMPORTANT: AI-g
 enerated works are NOT eligible. Open 14 May to 11 September 2026 (11:59 P
 M CET).\n\nOrganisation: PhotoVogue (Conde Nast)\nLocation: Online (global
 )\nAward: $12\,000 in total grants split across three artists: a $6\,000 O
 utstanding Vision Grant\, a $4\,000 Vision Grant\, and a $2\,000 Rising Vo
 ice Grant (emerging)\, plus presentation at the next PhotoVogue Festival\,
  potential publication across Vogue's global editions\, and PhotoVogue Vir
 tual Portfolio Reviews. Free to submit.\nDuration: One-off open call\n\nMo
 re: https://site.picter.com/photovogue-brave-new-visions-global-open-call-
 2026
URL:https://site.picter.com/photovogue-brave-new-visions-global-open-call-2
 026
LOCATION:Online (global)
END:VEVENT
